               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>This annotated manuscript of the <title xml:lang="sa">Amarakośa</title> has been bound together as a book with two other manuscripts. The folios have been bound out of order, and they have been renumbered, following the binding, from 96 onwards. Much of the original foliation has been lost due to damage, but the last folio is numbered, originally,  109.</p>
<p>The colophon gives a date of 1644, which Cabaton has interpreted as a Śāka date, corresponding to 1722.</p></summary>
                  
